                            The reasons advanced by Mani are not convincing. In principle, the introduction of GST has been an issue being debated for a decade. The opposition by Modi, as well as CMs of many states, were based on the question of compensation for loss of revenue. The centre has accepted that it will compensate for 5 years. While a cap of 18% sounds  good, it has to be seen what will be the real impact as GST has a cascading structure, with deductions on inputs. It will bring many, who are avoiding tax today, within the tax regime but the net effect is complex. The proposal that the GST council decides the rate is logical. The fact is a good law has been held up due to the Congress practicising blackmail tactics &amp; not on the basis of national interest.
